 According to [27], this algorithm can be summarized in 3 steps:

•Each cuckoo lays one egg at a time and dumps it in a randomly chosen nest;
•The best nests with the high quality of eggs will carry to the next generations;
•The number of available host nest is fixed and if a host bird identifies the cuckoo egg with the probability of \$p_{a}=[0,1]\$, then the host bird can either throw them away or abandon them and build a new nest.
